description: The negotiations come as the number of Chinese nationals crossing the U.S.-Mexico border without authorization rose to 24,000, an elevenfold increase over the prior year.
title: U.S. and China in high-level talks to deport more Chinese nationals, Mayorkas says

description: IDF spokesperson Rear Admiral Daniel Hagari said the World Central Kitchen volunteers had been mistaken for Hamas gunmen and that two officers involved in the operation had been dismissed. “This is a tragedy. It was a terrible chain of errors, and it should never have happened,” he said.
title: Israeli military accepts ‘full responsibility’ for killing WCK aid workers

description: Authorities in Ventura County, California, are investigating the death of Paul Kessler, a Jewish man who was injured during a confrontation at dueling rallies over Israel and Gaza died Monday, the sheriff’s department said.
title: Jewish man killed in altercation at dueling pro-Israel and pro-Palestinian rallies in California

description: Hani and Mahmoud Almadhoun have started a soup kitchen funded largely by online donations.
title: Gaza soup kitchen bridges efforts from brothers thousands of miles apart

description: The families of American citizens kidnapped by Hamas in Israel told NBC News’ Lester Holt that they decry the killings of innocent civilians in Gaza but pleaded with the international community to remain focused on the plight of their loved ones who are still in captivity.
title: Families of people kidnapped by Hamas deplore Gaza violence but demand release of hostages

description: Rachel Goldberg-Polin is fighting to bring home her son Hersh Goldberg-Polin, who was seized by Hamas from the Nova music festival on oct.7.
title: The mother of an Israeli hostage details her fight 6 months after the Hamas attack
